        <title>Data Management Plan</title>
        <description>Data generated in this project will be mainly imaging data, MALDI-MSI, spectral cytometry and omics data that will be deposited and made available upon reasonable request. In addition to image processing, graphical representation and statistical analysis will be performed. Data generated will be shared as research manuscripts that will be made available as pre-prints prior to publication in a peer-reviewed journal. In order to facilitate open science practices, findings will be disseminated through manuscript submission to scientific journals that promote open-peer review. Sequencing data will be made available in NCBI’s Gene Expression Omnibus. The OMERO suite will be used for sharing of large biological datasets, to allow data visualisation, organisation, analysis and sharing. All experimental data and associated protocols are stored in a dedicated server, where data generated by each researcher is organised in folders made accessible also to the PI.</description>
